      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ بَيْعِ اَلْغَزْلِ بِالثِّيَابِ اَلْمَنْسُوجَةِ وَ اَلْغَزْلُ أَكْثَرُ وَزْناً مِنَ اَلثِّيَابِ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3807 - Abdul-Rahman ibn Abi Abdullah narrated:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about selling yarn in exchange for woven clothes, where the yarn weighs more than the clothes.\nThe Imam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
